---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../../data/site.js';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const href = (url) => {
  if (url.startsWith('http')) return url;
  const cleanBase = base.endsWith('/') ? base.slice(0, -1) : base;
  const cleanUrl = url.startsWith('/') ? url : `/${url}`;
  return `${cleanBase}${cleanUrl}`;
};

const title = "Why New Managers Avoid Difficult Conversations and How to Stop";
const description = "Avoiding hard conversations doesn't keep the peace. It kills it. A simple script for new managers to address issues early and calmly.";
const topic = "Conflict";
const number = "07";
const longEmbed = null;
const longWatch = null;
const shorts = [];
const related = [
  {
    "title": "How to Manage Up Without Sounding Insecure as a New Manager",
    "slug": "/articles/manage-up-without-sounding-insecure/",
    "topic": "Managing Up"
  },
  {
    "title": "How to Run Your First Team Meeting Without Losing Control",
    "slug": "/articles/first-team-meeting-new-manager/",
    "topic": "Meetings"
  }
];

const bookUrl = href('/books/the-first-30-days-as-a-new-manager/');
const articlesUrl = href('/articles/');
const resourcesUrl = href('/resources/');

const schema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  headline: title,
  description,
  author: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: 'Plain Act',
  },
  publisher: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: 'Plain Act',
    url: site.siteUrl,
  },
  mainEntityOfPage: new URL(`${base}articles/difficult-conversations-new-manager/`, site.siteUrl).toString(),
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  path={`/articles/difficult-conversations-new-manager/`}
  schema={[schema]}
>
  <main class="article-page">
    <nav class="crumbs">
      <a href={articlesUrl}>Articles</a>
      <span>/</span>
      <span>{number}</span>
    </nav>

    <header class="article-hero">
      <p class="kicker">{topic}</p>
      <h1>{title}</h1>
      <p>{description}</p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href={bookUrl}>Read the book</a>
        <a href={resourcesUrl}>Resources</a>
        {longWatch && <a href={longWatch} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Watch video</a>}
      </div>
    </header>

    {longEmbed && (
      <section class="media-block">
        <div class="video-frame long">
          <iframe
            src={longEmbed}
            title={title}
            loading="lazy"
            allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
            allowfullscreen
          ></iframe>
        </div>
      </section>
    )}

    <article class="article-body">
      <h1>Why New Managers Avoid Difficult Conversations and How to Stop</h1>
<p>Difficult conversations don’t get easier with time.</p>
<p>They get more expensive.</p>
<p>New managers know something needs to be said. A missed standard, a bad attitude in meetings, tension between two people. You feel it on Monday. By Friday you still haven’t said anything. By next month, it’s a real problem, and now the conversation feels huge.</p>
<p>Avoidance doesn’t keep the peace. It rots it.</p>
<h2>What usually happens</h2>
<p>Someone is late repeatedly. You notice. You say nothing, because maybe it’s temporary.</p>
<p>Someone interrupts others in meetings. You cringe, but you move on.</p>
<p>Two team members clearly don’t work well together. You hope they sort it out.</p>
<p>You tell yourself: I don’t want to be that harsh new manager. I’ll wait and see. I’ll bring it up in the performance review.</p>
<p>The review is three months away. The behavior hardens into habit in three weeks.</p>
<p>When you finally speak, you’re frustrated, so your tone is sharp. The person is blindsided, because you never said anything before. Now it IS a big confrontation, exactly what you were trying to avoid.</p>
<h2>Why this becomes a problem</h2>
<p>Small issues become culture. What you tolerate, you teach. If lateness gets no response, lateness becomes normal. For everyone.</p>
<p>Trust drops. The rest of the team sees the issue. When you say nothing, they conclude you either don’t notice or don’t care. Both hurt.</p>
<p>You lose sleep over a 90-second conversation. Avoidance is exhausting. You replay the conversation in your head ten times instead of having it once out loud.</p>
<p>Conflict goes underground. People stop bringing issues to you, because you don’t address them. Then you hear about problems third-hand, too late.</p>
<h2>The mistake managers make</h2>
<p>The mistake is waiting until you feel ready.</p>
<p>You will never feel ready. Confidence does not come before the conversation. It comes after.</p>
<p>The other mistake is making it a personality talk. “You have a bad attitude.” That triggers defense instantly. Talk about behavior, not character. Behavior is fixable. Character feels like an attack.</p>
<h2>What to do instead</h2>
<p>Have it early. Have it short. Have it private. Use SBI: Situation. Behavior. Impact.</p>
<p><strong>1. Situation. Where and when.</strong> “I want to talk about yesterday’s standup.” Specific, recent, small.</p>
<p><strong>2. Behavior. What you saw.</strong> No labels. Just observable facts. “You interrupted Layla twice before she finished.” Not “you’re disrespectful.”</p>
<p><strong>3. Impact. What it caused.</strong> “It shut down the discussion and we missed her update.” One sentence.</p>
<p>Then pause. Ask: “What happened from your side?” Listen for 30 seconds.</p>
<p>Then close with one clear next step: “In meetings, let people finish before jumping in. Can you do that?”</p>
<p>Total time: under 3 minutes. Calm voice. Private room or call. Same day if possible, next day at latest.</p>
<p>If they get emotional, stay level. “I hear you. The expectation still stands.” You don’t need to win the debate. You need to set the standard clearly.</p>
<p>Write one line in your notes after: date, topic, agreed next step. That protects you if it repeats.</p>
<h2>Example</h2>
<p><strong>Avoided version:</strong> Three weeks of interrupting. Team morale drops. You finally snap in a meeting: “Can you just LET people talk for once?!” NowHR is involved.</p>
<p><strong>Early version, Day 2:</strong> “Hey, quick chat. Situation: today’s standup. Behavior: you cut in twice while Layla was presenting. Impact: we lost her numbers and had to follow up after. Next time, let her finish, then go. Good?”</p>
<p>Done. 45 seconds. No drama. Standard set. Most people correct immediately when it’s early and specific.</p>
<p>If it repeats, you have your note: “We talked about this on the 12th. It happened again today. This needs to change now.” Second conversation is firmer, because the first one was clear.</p>
<h2>How to apply this this week</h2>
<ol>
<li><strong>Name the one conversation you’re avoiding.</strong> Write it down. That’s your target. Have it within 48 hours.</li>
<li><strong>Script the three lines.</strong> Situation / Behavior / Impact. Write them before you walk in. Keeps you from rambling or softening.</li>
<li><strong>Do it private, do it early.</strong> Not in Slack, not in a meeting. 3 minutes, closed door, within 24 hours of the behavior.</li>
<li><strong>End with one next step, out loud.</strong> “Next time, do X.” Get a yes. That’s your agreement.</li>
<li><strong>Log it.</strong> Date, behavior, next step. If it never repeats, great. If it does, you have a clean record for conversation two.</li>
</ol>
<p>Do one hard conversation this week. Just one. It will be easier the second time. It will always be harder if you wait.</p>
<h2>Final note</h2>
<p>Difficult conversations are not cruel. Avoiding them is.</p>
<p>The kindest thing you can do as a new manager is address issues early, specifically, and calmly. People want to know where the line is. Tell them.</p>
<p>Early. Short. Private. SBI. Repeat.</p>
<p>This article is based on the Plain Act approach to early management pressure.</p>
<p>---</p>
    </article>

    {shorts.length > 0 && (
      <section class="shorts-section">
        <p class="kicker">Shorts</p>
        <h2>Short clips from this lesson</h2>
        <div class="shorts-grid">
          {shorts.map((short, index) => (
            <div class="short-frame">
              <iframe
                src={short.embed}
                title={`${title} short ${index + 1}`}
                loading="lazy"
                allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
                allowfullscreen
              ></iframe>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>
    )}

    <section class="cta-box">
      <p class="kicker">Plain Act</p>
      <h2>The First 30 Days as a New Manager</h2>
      <p>A practical manual for first-time managers carrying authority, feedback, delegation, and decision pressure.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href={bookUrl}>Open the book page</a>
        <a href={articlesUrl}>Back to articles</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="related">
      <p class="kicker">Related</p>
      <div class="related-grid">
        {related.map((item) => (
          <a class="related-card" href={href(item.slug)}>
            <span>{item.topic}</span>
            <strong>{item.title}</strong>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .article-page {
    max-width: 920px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2.6rem 1.2rem 4rem;
  }

  .crumbs {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.45rem;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .crumbs a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .article-hero {
    max-width: 780px;
  }

  .kicker {
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .article-hero h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(2.1rem, 5vw, 4.4rem);
    line-height: 0.96;
    letter-spacing: -0.06em;
  }

  .article-hero p {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 1.06rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .hero-actions {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.7rem;
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
  }

  .hero-actions a {
    color: var(--text);
    text-decoration: none;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 999px;
    padding: 0.55rem 0.82rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.035);
  }

  .media-block {
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .video-frame {
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 1rem;
    background: #05070a;
    box-shadow: 0 24px 70px rgba(0,0,0,.2);
  }

  .video-frame.long {
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
  }

  .video-frame iframe,
  .short-frame iframe {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    border: 0;
  }

  .article-body {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    padding: 1.2rem 0;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .article-body :global(h1) {
    display: none;
  }

  .article-body :global(h2) {
    margin-top: 2.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.7rem;
    font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 2.5vw, 2rem);
    letter-spacing: -0.035em;
  }

  .article-body :global(h3) {
    margin-top: 1.6rem;
  }

  .article-body :global(p),
  .article-body :global(li) {
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.78;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .article-body :global(strong) {
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .article-body :global(blockquote) {
    margin: 1.2rem 0;
    padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    background: rgba(255,255,255,.035);
    color: var(--text);
    border-radius: .75rem;
  }

  .shorts-section,
  .cta-box,
  .related {
    margin-top: 2.2rem;
  }

  .shorts-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: .85rem;
  }

  .short-frame {
    position: relative;
    aspect-ratio: 9 / 16;
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: .9rem;
    background: #05070a;
  }

  .cta-box {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 1.2rem;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,.035);
    padding: 1.2rem;
  }

  .cta-box h2 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(1.45rem, 3vw, 2.4rem);
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
  }

  .cta-box p {
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .related-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: .85rem;
  }

  .related-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: .45rem;
    color: var(--text);
    text-decoration: none;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,.035);
  }

  .related-card span {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: .75rem;
    letter-spacing: .12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .shorts-grid,
    .related-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
